\par 
\par 409.3. A creature\rquote s activated ability with the tap symbol in its activation cost can\rquote t be played unless the creature has been under its controller\rquote s control since the start of his or her most rec
ent turn. Creatures with haste may ignore this rule (see rule 502.5).
\par 
\par 409.4 A player can\rquote t begin to play a spell or activated ability that\rquote s prohibited from being played by an effect. 
\par }\pard\plain \s18\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f28\fs22\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\par 410. Handling Triggered Abilities
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s17\ql \fi-432\li749\ri0\widctlpar\tx440\tx740\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin749\itap0 \f28\fs22\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {410.1. Because they aren\rquote t played,
