\par 410.3. If multiple abilities have triggered since the last time a player received priority, pseudospells controlled by the active pla
yer go on the stack first, in any order he or she chooses, then those controlled by the opponent go on the stack in any order that opponent chooses. Then players once again check for and resolve state-based effects until none are generated, then abilities
