ther their controller intends to exercise the ability\rquote s option or not. (The choice is made when the ability resolves.) Likewise, triggered abilities that have an effect }{\i \'93unless\'94 }{
something is true or a player chooses to do something will go on the stack normally; the \'93unless\'94 part of the ability is dealt with when the ability resolves.
\par 
\par 410.6. An ability triggers only once each time its trigger event occurs. However, it can trigger repeatedly if one event contains multiple occurrences. See also rule 410.9.
\par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \li1440\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1440\itap0 \i\f29\fs22\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f28 Example:}{\f28  A permanent has an ability whose trigger condition reads, \'93
